{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cfabd651-7238-4d81-a7a4-6718104a5d39","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. MSTest v3 dropped support for older .NET Core / .NET runtimes. Here's the breakdown:\n\n| Target | MSTest v3 Compatible? |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Yes — .NET Framework 4.6.2+ is supported |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ No — .NET 5 is out of support; MSTest v3 requires **.NET 6+** |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ No — .NET Core 3.1 is out of support; MSTest v3 requires **.NET 6+** |\n\n**To migrate**, you'd need to update your target frameworks. For example, replace `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` with `net6.0` or `net8.0`. Then update the MSTest packages to v3 (`MSTest.TestFramework`, `MSTest.TestAdapter`), or switch to the unified `MSTest` meta-package.\n\nWould you like me to update the project file for you?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a834c0f7-3d1c-4f7f-ab32-672691ce6015","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is multi-targeting `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. MSTest v3 dropped support for older frameworks. Let me provide accurate information about compatibility issues.\n\nMSTest v3 key changes:\n- Minimum supported frameworks: .NET 6+ and .NET Framework 4.6.2+\n- `net5.0` is NOT supported (it's out of support and MSTest v3 requires .NET 6+)\n- `netcoreapp3.1` is NOT supported (MSTest v3 requires .NET 6+)\n- `net462` should be fine (MSTest v3 supports .NET Framework 4.6.2+)\n\n\n- This means the user will run into compatibility issues with `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` when trying to use MSTest v3.","outputTokens":460,"requestId":"240D:155659:48E3C1:4E0BED:6A03112F"},"id":"e11d6def-bf38-450d-a7f6-81fd8c600f94","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:38:37.551Z","parentId":"64b0ca5e-026b-481b-9947-143dc945c8a8"}
